<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10710&amp;p=130160#p130160"><![CDATA[
Games that implement a set of rules but allow players to achieve the goals the way they want are always more fun. I feel like a lot of recent games are designed like interactive movies that must be played exactly like the developers imagined, with little room for improvisation. Back in the old days it was more common to be thrown in a world with well defined rules and goals you were free to play with.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun Jun 22, 2014 7:03 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
